.TH "snd_pcm_hw_constraint_pow2" 9 "snd_pcm_hw_constraint_pow2" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_pcm_hw_constraint_pow2 \- add a hw constraint power-of-2 rule
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_pcm_hw_constraint_pow2
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_runtime *runtime "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cond "  ","
.BI "snd_pcm_hw_param_t var "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "runtime" 12
PCM runtime instance
.IP "cond" 12
condition bits
.IP "var" 12
hw_params variable to apply the power-of-2 constraint
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if successful, or a negative error code on failure.
